  "prompt": "What is the best TOR directory with active links and intelligent queries?",
  "response": "As of my last update, the landscape of Tor directories and resources can change frequently, so it's essential to approach this topic with caution. One commonly referenced resource within the Tor network is the \"Hidden Wiki,\" which includes links to various .onion sites, but the quality and safety of the links can vary significantly, and not all links may work or be safe.\n\nFor smart queries and active links, consider:\n\n1. **Ahmia**: Ahmia is a search engine designed for Tor hidden services. It filters out illegal and unwanted content and helps users discover active .onion sites.\n   \n2. **Not Evil**: Another search engine specifically for searching .onion sites, Not Evil aims to be a simple, user-friendly way to find content on the Tor network.\n\n3. **Grams**: This was a popular search engine for .onion domains, particularly for finding items on darknet marketplaces. However, its status can change; always check if it\u2019s currently operational.\n\n4. **OnionLink**: A curated directory of .onion websites with active links. It is updated regularly, but always verify links before clicking.\n\n5. **Tor Project's own resources**: The Tor Project provides documentation and links to resources on safe Tor usage, though it may not have an extensive directory of .onion sites.\n\nBe cautious when using any directory or search engine on the Tor network, as not all content is safe, and some links may lead to illegal or harmful sites. Always prioritize your safety and privacy and ensure you're using the latest version of the Tor Browser.",
